The motor is driven using PWM signals generated by the Arduino through the BTS7960 motor driver.

The encoder attached to the motor shaft generates pulses proportional to motor rotation. These pulses are read using Arduino interrupt pins to measure motor movement and response.

The PID controller continuously performs the following steps:

1. Read encoder feedback
2. Compare measured value with target setpoint
3. Calculate control error
4. Generate corrective PWM output
5. Drive motor using BTS7960

The PWM duty cycle is dynamically adjusted based on PID calculations to achieve stable motor behavior.

Pull-up resistors and capacitors were added to improve encoder signal reliability and reduce electrical noise generated by the motor.
